    ğŸ”¹ `--help`  --> â„¹ï¸ Displays the command help.
    ğŸ”¹ `--version` --> â„¹ï¸ Displays the program version.

ğŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ grub-mkrelpath /boot/grub/fonts/unicode.pf2
    
    ğŸ”¹ If you are in the `/` directory, the result will be `boot/grub/fonts/unicode.pf2`.

    $ grub-mkrelpath --directory=/boot/grub /boot/grub/fonts/unicode.pf2
    
    ğŸ”¹ The result will be `fonts/unicode.pf2`, because the path is calculated relative to `/boot/grub`.

